===Etymology===
From [[liver]] + Old English [[wort]] "plant", from the belief that some species looked like livers and were useful for treating the liver medicinally.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[bryophyte]] with a leafy stem or leafless [[thallus]] characterized by a dominant [[gametophyte]] stage and a lack of [[stoma]]ta on the [[sporophyte]] stage of the life cycle.

